(142, 1, '2025-10-31 02:20:40', '2025-10-31 02:20:40', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-large-font-size\">what is Sanrio?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":122,\"width\":\"840px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wptest01/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/sanrio-what-is-sanrio-1.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-122\" style=\"width:840px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Answering in real-world terms, Sanrio is a Japanese entertainment company. Its focus is bringing people into the magical world of everything cute and kawaii. Sanrio is known for super cute characters that everyone around the world knows and loves! That includes the kawaii superstar&nbsp;Hello Kitty and her cute Sanrio siblings like&nbsp;Kuromi,&nbsp;Pompompurin, the Little twin stars, and Hangyodon.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"28px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"font-size:28px\">When was sanrio created?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":140,\"width\":\"840px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wptest01/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Sanrio-Logo-history-768x512-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140\" style=\"width:840px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Sanrio’s journey into the kawaii sphere began when it was created on August 10, 1960. Back then though it wasn’t called Sanrio and it had nothing to do with the world of kawaii. It was called the Yamanashi Silk Company, a business focused on producing nice textiles. That’s a lot different from what Sanrio’s known for today!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"28px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"font-size:28px\">Who created sanrio?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":134,\"width\":\"840px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wptest01/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/creator-sanrio.avif\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-134\" style=\"width:840px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">The Yamanashi Silk Company was created by the Japanese entrepreneur Shintaro Tsuji. Expanding from silk to rubber sandals with flowery designs in 1962, Tsuji noticed that customers liked cute designs. He incorporated cute strawberry designs into the products he sold. They were a big hit! Seeing how cute designs did well in the market, Tsuji started using existing cartoon characters in the 60s like Snoopy. Eventually, he hired designers to create Sanrio cuties of his own like Hello Kitty, Cinnamoroll, Kuromi, and more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"28px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"font-size:28px\">How old is Sanrio?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":141,\"width\":\"840px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wptest01/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Hello-Kitty-50th_All-Characters.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-141\" style=\"width:840px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Shintaro Tsuji founded Sanrio on August 10, 1960, then known as the Yamanashi Silk Company using ¥1 million yen (roughly 5619 EUR) in capital. In 1962, Tsuji expanded his enterprise from silk to rubber sandals with flowers painted on them. It has been around for more than half a century! That\'s right, it\'s been making people smile with its kawaii characters for that long. We predict that Sanrio will keep making everyone happy for fifty, no a hundred years more to come, with all their Sanrio events and Sanrio merchandise!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"28px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"font-size:28px\">How many Sanrio characters are there?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":138,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wptest01/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/how-old-sanrio-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-138\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Since the creation of Hello Kitty, Sanrio has been pumping out kawaii characters for people to fall in love with. As of the moment, it has over 450 cuties with their own backstories and charm points. While most Sanrio characters are anthropomorphized animals, there are also some quirky humans, objects, and even food characters! Some of the most popular cuties from Sanrio are animals like Cinnamoroll, Pompompurin, Kuromi, My Melody, and more. If you\'d like to learn more about all the cuties that Sanrio has to offer, you can check out our Ultimate List of Sanrio characters! We have to warn you though, it can get really, really long!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"28px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"font-size:28px\">what does sanrio mean in japanese?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":136,\"width\":\"840px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wptest01/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/sanrio-what-does-sanrio-mean-in-japanese.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-136\" style=\"width:840px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Sanrio means <strong>\"Saint River\"</strong> in Spanish (\"San\" for Saint and \"Rio\" for River), a name chosen by the Japanese company\'s founder to inspire a peaceful culture where people can get along with each other. The name is linked to the idea of rivers where people first settled and is a reflection of the company\'s philosophy of spreading friendship, harmony, and smiles worldwide. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '61-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-31 02:20:40', '2025-10-31 02:20:40', '', 61, 'http://localhost/wptest01/?p=142', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
